 <html:p>Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> we must show that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}\colon  x = y \to  fx=fy]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/" title="Inverse" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/" type="local">invertible</fr:link>. By <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002C/" title="From quasi-inverses to coherent inverses" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002C/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002C/" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002C/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002C/" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002D/" title="From biinverses to quasi-inverses" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002D/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002D/" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002D/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-002D/" /></fr:link>, it suffices to exhibit a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000U/" title="Biinverse" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000U/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000U/" type="local">biinverse</fr:link> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{f}]]></fr:tex> (it is convenient that the underlying maps of the <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" type="local">section</fr:link> and <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" type="local">retraction</fr:link> need not be identical).</html:p>

 <html:p>We first define the <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" type="local">sections</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{x,y}\colon  fx = fy \to  x = y]]></fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is assumed to be <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" title="n-truncated map" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" type="local">propositional</fr:link>, we have by <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001R/" title="path object structure on fibers" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001R/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001R/" type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001R/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001R/" /></fr:link> an assignment <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi _{x,y}: \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
\cong _{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y,h^{-1}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>. We therefore define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{x,y}h :\equiv  
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \phi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
.1]]></fr:tex>; the witness of <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" type="local">sectionhood</fr:link> can be constructed using <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \phi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
.2]]></fr:tex> modulo some identification algebra.</html:p>

 <html:p>To construct the <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" type="local">retractions</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x,y}\colon  fx=fy\to  x = y]]></fr:tex>, we note by our assumption that we have an assignment <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi _{x,y}:\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen h:fx=fy\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}} 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x,\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 =_{\mathsf {fiber}\,f\,
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen fx\right \rparen \mathclose {}
} 
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen y,h^{-1}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>, and we define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{x,y}h :\equiv  \mathsf {act}_{-.1}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \psi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
]]></fr:tex>. It remains to show that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x,y:A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h\colon  x =y]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{-.1}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \psi _{x,y}h\right \rparen \mathclose {}
=h]]></fr:tex>. By induction on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h]]></fr:tex> it suffices to show that for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x:A]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {act}_{-.1}
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen \psi _{x,x}\mathsf {refl}\right \rparen \mathclose {}
 = \mathsf {refl}]]></fr:tex>. We will deduce that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\psi _{x,x}\mathsf {refl} = \mathsf {refl}]]></fr:tex> from our assumption that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" title="n-truncated map" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" type="local">propositional</fr:link> and thus <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" title="n-truncated map" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001T/" type="local">fibred in sets</fr:link> via <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001L/" title="propositions are sets" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001L/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001L/" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001L/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-001L/" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
