            <fr:route>/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000W/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Inverse">Inverse</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>An <html:em><html:strong>inverse</html:strong></html:em> to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000X/" title="Quasi-inverse" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000X/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000X/" type="local">quasi-inverse</fr:link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\chi  \colon  \mathsf {act}_{f}\circ  \eta  \sim  \epsilon \circ  f]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  g \circ  f \sim  f]]></fr:tex> relating the (<html:em>a priori</html:em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> equipped with an inverse as an <html:em><html:strong>invertible function</html:strong></html:em>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>12</fr:month>
              <fr:day>19</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000X/</fr:uri>
            <fr:display-uri>https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000X/</fr:display-uri>
            <fr:route>/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000X/</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Quasi-inverse">Quasi-inverse</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source">
  
  
  <fr:link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</fr:link>
</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A <html:em><html:strong>quasi-inverse</html:strong></html:em> to a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f \colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex> is a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g \colon  B \to  A]]></fr:tex> equipped with homotopies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon \colon  f \circ  g \sim  1_{B}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta \colon  g \circ  f \sim 1_{A}]]></fr:tex>, rendering <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g]]></fr:tex> simultaneously a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" type="local">section</fr:link> and a <fr:link href="/foreign/erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" title="Section-retraction pair" uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" display-uri="https://erct.jonmsterling.com/erct-000Y/" type="local">retraction</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\epsilon ]]></fr:tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <html:em>unit</html:em> and <html:em>counit</html:em> of the quasi-inverse.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
